OL,3,CBBC One and ITV 1 News at Ten: the
OL,4,Clegacy of a bad decision in 1998
OL,6,FThe BBC ` during a competitive period
OL,7,Funder Greg Dyke ` moved the BBC News
OL,8,Fat Nine back by an hour. The original
OL,9,Fplan to do this in the autumn of 2001
OL,10,Fwas abandoned and instead put into
OL,11,Faction at breakneck speed. The BBC
OL,12,Fprogramme launched in October 2000.
OL,14,FIn 2004 ITV put up the white flag and
OL,15,Fmoved its late news back to 10.30pm.
OL,17,FThen Michael Grade, as ITV's executive
OL,18,Fchairman, reinstated News at Ten in
OL,19,F2008.
